gate: LOCKED
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: Memoize track.points → [lat,lon][] conversion in TrackingActionScreen

context: |
  TrackingActionScreen.tsx passes track points to TrackingRouteMap as:
    track.points.map(p => [p.latitude, p.longitude])

  This inline .map() creates a new array reference on every render of
  TrackingActionScreen, which causes ImperativePlaybackMarker (a map child)
  to see changed props and potentially re-run its useEffect even when the
  track data hasn't changed.

  The conversion belongs in a useMemo with [track] dependency, not inline JSX.

steps:
  - In TrackingActionScreen.tsx: add useMemo for playbackPoints:
      const playbackPoints = useMemo(
        () => track?.points.map(p => [p.latitude, p.longitude] as [number, number]) ?? [],
        [track]
      )
  - Pass playbackPoints to TrackingRouteMap instead of inline map()
  - Update TrackingRouteMap props interface if the prop name differs
  - Run tsc --noEmit

done: [playbackPoints memoized, tsc exits 0]
out:
  - src-client/src/components/screens/tracking-screen/TrackingActionScreen.tsx
  - src-client/src/components/screens/tracking-screen/components/TrackingRouteMap.tsx
